column4: <content>Martin van Cleve. Catalogue. Master Drawings exhibited by Bernard Houthakker 1971 (Amsterdam) 98 Rokin (manager director L.A. Houthakker) Maerten van Cleve; 12. Lent surprising ravellers at their Carnival meal. Pen and brown wash, 184 x 275 mm from the collection of Prince Argoutinsky-Dolgoroukoff and Robert Witt (= Interior with fat peasants at table, sausages & hams hanging down from ceiling (like in Bruegel's Fat kitchen). In the window a small nude female figure with a cap. Figure (Lent?) appears, against which a man raises a stick to hit her. Is this Lent or a variant of subject of Bruegel's Fat Kitchen?</content>
